cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.SY

This paper deals with image manipulation using a combination of symbolic programs and neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves learning from a single image and using internal statistics, which suggests the involvement of machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. The use of neural networks also suggests the involvement of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible sub-category. The paper also involves reasoning over repetition and symmetry, which suggests the involvement of cs.GR (Graphics) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the use of symbolic programs suggests the involvement of cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a possible sub-category.
